HEADWORD: Booking clerk
<hw>Book"ing clerk`</hw> <pr>(b⟦oocr⟧k"⟦icr⟧ng kl⟦etil⟧rk`; Eng.
kl⟦aum⟧rk`)</pr>. <def>A clerk who registers passengers, baggage, etc.,
for conveyance, as by railway or steamship, or who sells passage tickets
at a booking office.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Booking office</ent>⟦br⟧
